This directory contains source files to create the `masc' compiler.

MASC takes as its input a source file containing a system definition.
The MASC source language is described elsewhere. From this defintion it
creates :

	* a `C' program containing the instructions necessary to instantiate
	the system described by the MASC source program; this program
	may be called in a number of ways. By default, it installs the
	system on the host machine, but by calling it with the -remote
	option, the system may be installed over a network

	* `agent views' of the organisation described by the MASC source 
	program. One agent view is generated for each agent, in the appropriate
	destination language.  By default, the filenames are generated by
	prefixing the agent name with `view_' and appending the extension
	`.p', `.lsp' or `.pl'.
